Version 1.0.0
- Let's pretend this hasn't been released yet - Major overhaul to the health and damage of supermobs - Fixed bug where blazes were doing too much damage - Armor is now far more important than it used to be - Cleaned up the scanner -

Version 1.0.0
- Fixed metadataKiller bug

Version 1.0.0
- Fixed natural mob spawning issue - Fixed loot issue - Completed the switch to level-based mob scaling - Made it so natural mobs mixing with artifical ones results in artificial mobs - Mobs spawned by plugins are now considered natural - Removed stupid attempt at making vanishnopacket compatibility - Improved the visual effects a bit more

Version 1.0.0
- Now cancelling entity explosion damage (due to creeper radius)

Version 1.0.0
- Now properly accounting for invalid commands

Version 0.0.23
- There have been 23 commits pushed to GitHub, so I might as well call this version 23. Not ready for 1.0.0 yet. - Rewrote all of the visual effects, now they support larger amounts of items per track and minor power visual effects stack on the same track while keeping the same distance between them.

Version 0.0.25
- Remembered how to count - Added config options for many, many things, untested so they probably don't work properly yet - Config-related tweaks to the code, which now allows weirder scenarios with entire sections disabled

Version 0.0.26
- Loot is now its own yml file - Added more config options - Tweaked config-related variables - Reworked all commands, fixed miscellaneous bugs in them - Tweaked few settings to fully implement iron golems as aggressive stacking entities

Version 0.0.27
- Fixed iron golem extra stats - Added initial spawnmob command - Last planned features before 1.0.0 are now done, only (possible) bugfixes left before upload

Version 1.0.0
- First public release - Magmasmobs project renamed to EliteMobs - Added a metadata flush method, more organized metadata handling - Fixed fall damage

Version 1.1.0
- Just bug fixes - Fixed level 1 mobs being somewhat unkillable (level 1 mobs aren't supposed to exist anyway) - Fixed gold boots speed power not working - An issue still remains when two manually spawned mobs merge leaving some vestige visual effects behind

Version 1.1.1
- Streamlined minor power making process a bit - Added FireAttack minor power - Fixed ranged mobs not having attack powers

Version 1.1.2
- Added Invisibility minor power
